results.name: Impulse-Control Disorder
results.definition: A category of behaviors that can be loosely defined as the failure to resist an impulsive act or behavior that may be harmful to self or others.

results.name: Stargardt Disease
results.definition: An autosomal recessive and rarely autosomal dominant inherited disorder caused by mutations in the ABCA4 or ELOVL4 genes respectively. It is characterized by macular degeneration that begins in late childhood resulting in progressive loss of vision.

results.name: Dubin-Johnson Syndrome
results.definition: An inherited autosomal recessive disorder characterized by the presence of mild jaundice due to abnormalities in the bilirubin transportation from the liver parenchyma to the biliary system.
results.glossary_definition: A benign, autosomally recessive inherited hyperbilirubinemia characterized by the presence of a dark pigment in the centrilobular region of the liver cells. There is a functional defect in biliary excretion of bilirubin, cholephilic dyes, and porphyrins. Affected persons may be asymptomatic or have vague constitutional or gastrointestinal symptoms. The liver may be slightly enlarged, and oral and intravenous cholangiography fails to visualize the biliary tract.

results.name: Babesiosis
results.definition: A parasitic infection caused by Babesia. It is transmitted by ticks and infects the red blood cells. Signs and symptoms include fever, fatigue and hemolytic anemia.

results.name: Choledochal Cyst
results.definition: Cystic dilatation of the hepatic duct or bile duct.
results.glossary_definition: A congenital cystic dilatation of the common bile duct; this condition may be asymptomatic, or cause vomiting, fever, jaundice, or pain in the right upper quadrant.

results.name: Stage 0 Rectal Cancer
match: Carcinoma in situ of the Rectum
search: Carcinoma in situ of the Rectum
results.definition: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ: intraepithelial or invasion of the lamina propria. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)
synonyms: Carcinoma in situ of the Rectum

results.name: Familial Hypertrophic Cardiomyopathy
results.definition: Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy caused by mutations in the genes encoding components of the sarcomere, in the absence of predisposing conditions.

results.name: Hypertension
results.definition: Blood pressure that is abnormally high.
results.glossary_definition: A blood pressure of 140/90 or higher. High blood pressure usually has no symptoms. It can harm the arteries and cause an increase in the risk of stroke, heart attack, kidney failure, and blindness.

results.name: Endocervical Carcinoma
results.definition: An adenocarcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelium resembling the endocervical epithelium.

results.name: Jervell and Lange Nielsen Syndrome
results.definition: An autosomal recessive inherited syndrome caused by mutations in the KCNE1 and KCNQ1 genes. It is characterized by congenital hearing loss and arrhythmia. It is a form of long QT syndrome.

results.name: Tracheal Sarcoma
results.definition: A rare malignant soft tissue neoplasm that arises from the trachea.

results.name: Liver Leiomyoma
results.definition: A benign smooth muscle neoplasm arising from the liver. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with cigar-shaped nuclei, interlacing fascicles, and a whorled pattern.
ancestors: Liver and Intrahepatic Bile Duct Neoplasm

results.name: Glomus Tumor of the Skin
results.definition: A glomus tumor arising from the skin. It usually presents as a small red-blue nodule and it often associated with pain at the site.

results.name: Liddle Syndrome
results.definition: An autosomal dominant inherited syndrome caused by dysregulation of the amiloride-sensitive sodium channel. It is characterized by early onset hypertension, hypokalemia, metabolic alkalosis, low plasma renin and hypoaldosteronism.

results.name: Dilated Cardiomyopathy
results.definition: Cardiomyopathy which is characterized by dilation and contractile dysfunction of the left and right ventricles. It may be idiopathic, or it may result from a myocardial infarction, myocardial infection, or alcohol abuse. It is a cause of congestive heart failure.

results.name: Lymphangioma
results.definition: A benign lesion composed of dilated lymphatic channels. Painless swelling is the usual clinical manifestation.
results.glossary_definition: A benign neoplasm arising from the lymphatics.

results.oncotree_disease: Pineal Parenchymal Tumor of Intermediate Differentiation
results.definition: A WHO grade II or III pineal parenchymal neoplasm of intermediate-grade malignancy, affecting all ages. It is composed of diffuse sheets or large lobules of uniform cells with mild to moderate nuclear atypia and low to moderate level mitotic activity. (Adapted from WHO)
synonyms: Pineal Parenchymal Tumor of Intermediate Differentiation
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Acquired Color Blindness
results.definition: Non-heritable difficulty in distinguishing colors.
results.glossary_definition: Non-heritable difficulty in distinguishing colors.

results.name: Nystagmus
results.definition: Involuntary movements of the eyeballs. The presence or absence of nystagmus is often used in the diagnosis of a variety of neurological and visual disorders.
results.glossary_definition: Repetitive and involuntary movement of the eyes.

results.name: Hemorrhagic Cystitis
results.definition: Inflammation of the bladder resulting in bloody urine.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the bladder resulting in bloody urine.

results.name: Ovarian Leiomyosarcoma
results.definition: An aggressive malignant smooth muscle neoplasm, arising from the ovary. It is characterized by a proliferation of neoplastic spindle cells.

results.name: Urethra Disorder
results.definition: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the urethra.

results.name: Vulvar Dystrophy
results.definition: A non-neoplastic lesion that affects the vulva and is characterized by thinning or thickening of the skin and dryness.

results.name: Parasagittal Meningioma
results.definition: A meningioma that affects the falx cerebri.

results.name: Immature Ovarian Teratoma
match: Immature Germ Cell Teratoma of Ovary
Immature Germ Cell Teratoma of the Ovary
Malignant Germ Cell Teratoma of Ovary
Malignant Germ Cell Teratoma of the Ovary
search: Immature Germ Cell Teratoma of Ovary
Immature Germ Cell Teratoma of the Ovary
Malignant Germ Cell Teratoma of Ovary
Malignant Germ Cell Teratoma of the Ovary
results.definition: A malignant germ cell tumor arising from the ovary. It usually affects females in their first two decades of life. It contains variable amounts of immature embryonal tissues. Based on the amount of immature neuroepithelial component, immature teratomas are graded from 1 to 3. The stage and grade of the tumor and the grade of the metastatic tumor are the important factors that predict prognosis. The use of cisplatin-based combination chemotherapy has significantly improved the survival rates of the patients.
synonyms: Immature Germ Cell Teratoma of Ovary
Immature Germ Cell Teratoma of the Ovary
Malignant Germ Cell Teratoma of Ovary
Malignant Germ Cell Teratoma of the Ovary

results.name: Meningeal Melanomatosis
results.definition: A meningeal melanoma with secondary diffuse meningeal spread. (WHO)

results.name: Hereditary Wilms Tumor
results.definition: Familial embryonal neoplasm derived from nephrogenic blastemal cells. Several lines of differentiation, including blastemal, stromal and epithelial, are usually expressed. Comprises approximately 1% of Wilms tumors. (AFIP fascicle version 2.0)

results.name: Alcoholic Polyneuropathy
results.definition: Any disease affecting more than one nerve.

results.name: Farmer's Lung
results.definition: Hypersensitivity pneumonitis caused by the repeated exposure and inhalation of biological dust (such as hay dust, mold spores, or other agricultural products). It is considered a type II hypersensitivity inflammatory reaction. In the acute phase, signs and symptoms include fever, chills, cough, dyspnea, headache, and chest tightness. The subacute phase manifests as chronic cough, dyspnea, anorexia, and weight loss. The chronic phase results from the prolonged exposure to the antigen and is characterized by severe dyspnea and irreversible damage to the lungs.
results.glossary_definition: Systemic and pulmonary reactions resulting from inhalation of dust from moldy hay, threshing dust, or moldy straw, by persons who have become hypersensitive to antigens in the dust. It is most often associated with inhalation of spores of Micromonospora faeni or Thermoactinomyces vulgaris. (From Dorland, 27th ed)

results.name: Paralytic Ileus
results.definition: An ileus caused by abdominal or pelvic surgery, infections, disorders that affect the muscles and nerves, and medications. Signs and symptoms include those of intestinal obstruction.
results.glossary_definition: A condition in which the muscles of the intestines do not allow food to pass through, resulting in a blocked intestine. Paralytic ileus may be caused by surgery, inflammation, and certain drugs.

results.name: Fabry Disease
results.definition: A rare X-linked inherited lysosomal storage disorder characterized by deficiency of the enzyme alpha-galactosidase A. It results in the accumulation of glycolipids in the blood vessels and tissues. Signs and symptoms include hypertension, cardiomyopathy, angiokeratomas, neuropathy, hypohidrosis, keratopathy, proteinuria, and renal failure.

results.name: Uveal Neoplasm
results.definition: A neoplasm that affects the uvea. Uveal melanoma is a representative example.

results.name: Vulvar Non-Keratinizing Squamous Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the vulva and is characterized by the absence of keratin pearls.

results.name: Multiple Skull Base Meningiomas
results.definition: Multiple meningiomas that affect the skull base.

results.name: Mesonephric Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: An adenocarcinoma of the cervix or the vagina arising from mesonephric remnants.

results.name: Thoracic Outlet Syndrome
results.definition: A syndrome resulting from the compression of the blood vessels or nerves in the space between the clavicle and first rib (thoracic outlet). It is caused by car accident injuries or repetitive job or sport-related injuries. Signs and symptoms include pain in the shoulders and neck, numbness in the fingers, and weakening grip.

results.definition: A rare malignant neoplasm with melanocytic differentiation characterized by the presence of polygonal or spindle shaped clear cells. This sarcoma usually affects the tendons and aponeuroses and is associated with a poor prognosis due to recurrences and metastases.
results.glossary_definition: A soft tissue tumor that begins in a tendon (tough, fibrous, cord-like tissue that connects muscle to bone or to another structure). Clear cell sarcoma of soft tissue has certain markers that are also found on malignant melanoma (a type of skin cancer). It usually occurs in the leg or arm.

results.name: Thyroiditis
results.definition: Inflammation of the thyroid gland. This category includes Hashimoto thyroiditis, Riedel thyroiditis, acute thyroiditis, subacute thyroiditis, and radiation-induced thyroiditis.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the thyroid gland. Thyroiditis may be an autoimmune disease that affects the thyroid gland over time, causing hypothyroidism (too little thyroid hormone). A temporary form of thyroiditis may also occur after the birth of a baby, or when viral or bacterial infections spread to the thyroid.

results.name: Obesity
results.definition: Having a high amount of body fat (body mass index [BMI] of 30 or more).
results.glossary_definition: A condition marked by an abnormally high, unhealthy amount of body fat.

results.name: Isovaleric Acidemia
results.definition: A rare autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the IVD gene. It is characterized by abnormalities in the metabolism of leucine. Signs and symptoms vary from very mild to life threatening and include vomiting, seizures, lethargy, and coma.

results.name: Choroid Spindle Cell Melanoma
match: Spindle Cell Melanoma of the Choroid
search: Spindle Cell Melanoma of the Choroid
synonyms: Spindle Cell Melanoma of the Choroid

results.name: Popliteal Pterygium Syndrome
results.definition: A rare, autosomal dominant inherited syndrome caused by mutations in the IRF6 gene. It is characterized by the presence of cleft palate, cleft lip, pits in the lower lip, web behind the knee (popliteal pterygium), syndactyly, cryptorchidism, scrotal malformation, and hypoplasia of the labia majora.

results.name: Superficial Basal Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A variant of basal cell carcinoma of the skin presenting as erythematous, often multiple patches. Morphologically, it is characterized by the presence of superficial lobules of basaloid cells projecting into the dermis. The basaloid cell lobules are surrounded by myxoid stroma and are usually confined to the papillary dermis.

results.name: Childhood Extraocular Retinoblastoma
results.definition: Retinoblastoma during childhood that has spread beyond the eye.

results.name: Renal Pelvis Papillary Urothelial Carcinoma
match: Papillary Carcinoma of the Kidney Pelvis
Papillary Carcinoma of the Renal Pelvis
search: Papillary Carcinoma of the Kidney Pelvis
Papillary Carcinoma of the Renal Pelvis
results.definition: A papillary transitional cell carcinoma that arises from the renal pelvis.
synonyms: Papillary Carcinoma of the Kidney Pelvis
Papillary Carcinoma of the Renal Pelvis
ancestors: Renal Pelvis and Ureter Urothelial Carcinoma

results.name: Focal Glomerulonephritis
results.definition: Inflammation of a specific segment of glomeruli within the kidney.

results.name: Benign Mediastinal Psammomatous Schwannoma
match: Benign Psammomatous Neurilemmoma of the Mediastinum
Benign Psammomatous Schwannoma of the Mediastinum
search: Benign Psammomatous Neurilemmoma of the Mediastinum
Benign Psammomatous Schwannoma of the Mediastinum
results.definition: A schwannoma that arises from the posterior mediastinum. It is characterized by the presence of psammoma bodies.
synonyms: Benign Psammomatous Neurilemmoma of the Mediastinum
Benign Psammomatous Schwannoma of the Mediastinum
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Necrotizing Fasciitis
results.definition: Infection of the deep skin and subcutaneous tissues and necrosis of the fascia. It is caused by bacteria including group A streptococcus, Staphylococcus aureus and Clostridium perfringens. It may develop following trauma and invasive procedures.

results.name: T-Cell Immunodeficiency
results.definition: A broad classification of disorders that affect the cell-mediated aspect of the immune response. Circulating numbers of T lymphocytes are decreased or ineffective.

results.name: Intermittent Explosive Disorder
results.definition: A disorder characterized by recurrent episodes of serious assaultive acts or destruction of property due to a failure to resist aggressive impulses; the degree of aggression during these episodes is grossly out of proportion to any psychosocial provocation. The aggressive episodes are not etiologically linked to another mental disorder, a general medical condition, or substance use.

results.name: Myositis
results.definition: An inflammatory process affecting the skeletal muscles. Causes include infections, injuries, and autoimmune disorders.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation affecting the skeletal muscles.

results.name: Post-Streptococcal Glomerulonephritis
results.definition: Inflammation of the glomeruli status post infection with nephritogenic streptococci, most often group A beta hemolytic streptococcus.

results.name: Mycetoma
results.definition: A chronic granulomatous inflammation involving the deep dermis and the subcutaneous tissues. It is caused by fungi and actinomycetes.

results.name: Thymic Adenosquamous Carcinoma
results.definition: A rare carcinoma that arises from the thymus and is characterized by the presence of glandular and squamous carcinomatous components.

results.name: Thymoma
results.definition: A neoplasm arising from the epithelial cells of the thymus. Although thymomas are usually encapsulated tumors, they may invade the capsule and infiltrate the surrounding tissues or even metastasize to distant anatomic sites. The following morphologic subtypes are currently recognized: type A, type B, type AB, metaplastic, micronodular, microscopic, and sclerosing thymoma. Thymomas type B are further subdivided into types B1, B2, and B3. Thymoma type B3 usually has the most aggressive clinical course.
results.glossary_definition: A tumor of the thymus, an organ that is part of the lymphatic system and is located in the chest, behind the breastbone.

results.name: Inner Ear Lipoma
match: Lipoma of the Internal Auditory Canal
search: Lipoma of the Internal Auditory Canal
results.definition: A rare benign adipose tissue neoplasm of the internal auditory canal, often presenting as an acoustic tumor. It may be intermixed with the vestibulocochlear nerve and may adhere to adjacent structures.
synonyms: Lipoma of the Internal Auditory Canal
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Meckel Diverticulitis
results.definition: Inflammation of a congenital diverticulum of the lower intestine.

results.name: Verrucous Hemangioma
results.definition: A skin hemangioma characterized by the presence of epidermal hyperplasia.

results.name: Hyperostosis
results.definition: Excessive thickening of bone.
results.glossary_definition: Increase in the mass of bone per unit volume.

results.name: Breast Leiomyoma
results.definition: A well-circumscribed benign smooth muscle neoplasm arising from the breast. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with cigar-shaped nuclei, interlacing fascicles, and a whorled pattern.

results.name: Small Intestine Leiomyosarcoma
results.definition: An aggressive malignant smooth muscle neoplasm, arising from the small intestine. It is characterized by a proliferation of neoplastic spindle cells.

results.name: Malignant Tongue Neoplasm
results.definition: A malignant neoplasm affecting the tongue. The vast majority of cases are carcinomas.

results.name: Testicular Lymphoma
results.definition: A lymphoma that arises from the testis and is not associated with lymphoma in another anatomic site.

results.name: Obstructive Uropathy
results.definition: Uropathy that is caused by an impediment to flow in the urinary tract.

results.name: Iritis
results.definition: Inflammation of the iris.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the iris.

results.name: Testicular Spermatocytic Seminoma
results.definition: A rare variant of seminoma characterized by the presence of three cell types: round cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm, small cells with dark nucleus and a small amount of cytoplasm, and mono-or multinucleated giant cells. The neoplastic cells are not cohesive. There is an edematous stroma present; lymphocytic infiltrates are rarely seen. Most patients are older males.

results.name: Well Differentiated Papillary Mesothelioma
match: Well-Differentiated Papillary Neoplasm of the Mesothelium
Well-Differentiated Papillary Tumor of the Mesothelium
search: Well-Differentiated Papillary Neoplasm of the Mesothelium
Well-Differentiated Papillary Tumor of the Mesothelium
results.definition: A localized or multifocal mesothelioma arising from the peritoneum and less often the pleura. Cases arising from the peritoneum predominantly occur in women. It is characterized by the formation of papillae, covered by a single layer of blunt mesothelial cells. Mitotic figures are not present. There is no evidence of severe cytologic atypia. It has a relatively favorable clinical outcome, compared to malignant mesothelioma.
synonyms: Well-Differentiated Papillary Neoplasm of the Mesothelium
Well-Differentiated Papillary Tumor of the Mesothelium

results.name: Myeloid Sarcoma
results.definition: A tumor mass composed of myeloblasts or immature myeloid cells. It occurs in extramedullary sites or the bone. (WHO, 2001)
results.glossary_definition: A malignant, green-colored tumor of myeloid cells (a type of immature white blood cell). This tumor is usually associated with myelogenous leukemia.

results.name: Scirrhous Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: An infiltrating adenocarcinoma characterized by the presence of desmoplastic stromal reaction.
results.glossary_definition: An adenocarcinoma with a hard (Greek skirrhos, hard) structure owing to the formation of dense connective tissue in the stroma. (From Dorland, 27th ed)

results.name: Syringoma
results.definition: A benign sweat gland neoplasm usually affecting the lower eyelids and upper cheeks. The lesions are papular and are usually numerous. Morphologically, there are nests, cords, and tubules of epithelial cells present, surrounded by a dense stroma in the reticular dermis.
results.glossary_definition: A benign tumor of the sweat glands which is usually multiple and results from malformation of sweat ducts. It is uncommon and more common in females than in males. It is most likely to appear at adolescence, and further lesions may develop during adult life. It does not appear to be hereditary. (Rook et al., Textbook of Dermatology, 4th ed, pp2407-8)

results.name: Rosacea
results.definition: A chronic erythematous skin disorder that affects the face. It is characterized by the development of redness in the cheeks, nose, and/or forehead and telangiectasia. Sometimes, the erythematous changes may involve the eyelids.
results.glossary_definition: A chronic dermatitis characterized by redness, flushing, pustules and papules on the face.

results.name: Brain Stem Ependymoma
results.definition: An ependymoma that arises from the brain stem.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Migraine
results.definition: A common, severe type of vascular headache often associated with increased sympathetic activity, resulting in nausea, vomiting, and light sensitivity.
results.glossary_definition: A headache disorder characterized by recurrent episodes of moderate to severe pulsating pain, and may be associated with nausea, vomiting, photophobia , phonophobia, and worsening with exertion.

results.name: Papillary Squamous Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: A well differentiated squamous cell carcinoma characterized by a papillary, exophytic growth pattern and hyperkeratosis. The most commonly affected anatomic sites are the larynx, penis, cervix, vagina, and vulva.

results.name: Placenta Previa
results.definition: A condition in which the placenta covers or is within 1 cm of the cervical os.
results.glossary_definition: A placenta which develops in the lower uterine segment, in the zone of dilatation, so that it covers or adjoins the internal os. Painless hemorrhage in the last trimester, particularly during the eighth month, is the most common symptom. (Dorland, 27th ed)

results.name: Autonomic Nervous System Neoplasm
match: Neoplasm of the Autonomic Nervous System
Tumor of the Autonomic Nervous System
search: Neoplasm of the Autonomic Nervous System
Tumor of the Autonomic Nervous System
results.definition: Benign and malignant neoplasms which arise from or directly involve the central or peripheral elements of the autonomic nervous system.
synonyms: Neoplasm of the Autonomic Nervous System
Tumor of the Autonomic Nervous System

results.name: Rothmund-Thomson Syndrome
results.definition: An autosomal recessive inherited syndrome usually caused by mutations in the RECQL4 gene. It is characterized by poikilodermatous skin changes, sparse hair, cataracts, small stature, skeletal abnormalities, and an increased predisposition to cancer, particularly osteosarcoma.
results.glossary_definition: A rare inherited disorder that affects the skin and many other parts of the body, including the bones, eyes, nose, hair, nails, teeth, testes, and ovaries. People with Rothmund-Thomson syndrome have an increased risk of osteosarcoma (bone cancer).

results.name: Porphyria Cutanea Tarda
results.definition: A cutaneous form of the genetic photosensitive disease, porphyria, that is characterized by onset in adult life and the presence of scarring bullae, hyperpigmentation, facial hypertrichosis, and sometimes sclerodermatous thickenings and alopecia. Uroporphyrins are found in the urine due to a deficiency of uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase, an enzyme required for the synthesis of heme.

results.name: Myxopapillary Ependymoma
results.definition: A slow growing, WHO grade I glioma which generally occurs in young adults. It arises almost exclusively in the conus medullaris, cauda equina, and filum terminale of the spinal cord. It generally has a favorable prognosis and is characterized histologically by tumor cells arranged in a papillary manner around vascularized mucoid stromal cores. (Adapted from WHO).
results.glossary_definition: A benign neoplasm of ependymal origin.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Dysthymic Disorder
results.definition: A chronic mood disorder in which the symptoms are similar to, though milder than, those diagnosed in depression.
results.glossary_definition: Chronically depressed mood that occurs for most of the day more days than not for at least 2 years. The required minimum duration in children to make this diagnosis is 1 year. During periods of depressed mood, at least 2 of the following additional symptoms are present: poor appetite or overeating, insomnia or hypersomnia, low energy or fatigue, low self esteem, poor concentration or difficulty making decisions, and feelings of hopelessness. (DSM-IV)

results.name: Cutaneous Lymphangioma
results.definition: A lymphangioma arising from the skin.

results.name: Ovarian Mixed Germ Cell Tumor
match: Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm of Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm of the Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Tumor of Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Tumor of the Ovary
search: Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm of Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm of the Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Tumor of Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Tumor of the Ovary
results.definition: An ovarian malignant germ cell tumor characterized by the presence of at least two different germ cell components. At least one of the germ cell components is primitive. The most common combination of germ cell elements is dysgerminoma and yolk sac tumor.
synonyms: Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm of Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Neoplasm of the Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Tumor of Ovary
Mixed Germ Cell Tumor of the Ovary

results.name: Glycogen Storage Disease Type IV
results.definition: A rare inherited type of glycogen storage disease caused by deficiency of amylo-1,4-1,6 transglucosidase.

results.name: Helminthiasis
results.definition: A parasitic infection characterized by the infestation with worms, mainly in the intestine.

results.name: Chondrodysplasia Punctata
results.definition: A rare congenital developmental disorder characterized by the presence of stippled foci of calcification in the hyaline cartilage, joint contractions, mental retardation and ichthyosis.

results.name: Glandular Papillomatosis
results.definition: Multifocal neoplastic proliferations of the glandular epithelium displaying a papillary pattern.

results.name: Caroli Disease
results.definition: A rare congenital disorder characterized by cystic dilatation of the intrahepatic bile ducts. It is associated with cholangitis and the formation of stones.

results.name: Collagenous Colitis
results.definition: A type of microscopic colitis of unknown etiology. It is characterized by the presence of collagen deposits in the lamina propria of the colonic mucosa. Patients present with chronic watery diarrhea. Colonoscopy reveals normal-appearing mucosa. The diagnosis is made with the microscopic examination of the colonic biopsy samples.

results.name: Amebiasis
results.definition: A parasitic infectious disorder caused by amoebas. The parasite may cause colitis which is manifested with bloody diarrhea, abdominal pain, nausea and fever. In rare cases it may spread to the liver, brain and lungs.

results.name: Glycogen Storage Disease Type II
results.definition: An autosomal recessive inherited type of glycogen storage disease caused by deficiency of the enzyme acid alpha-glucosidase. It results in the abnormal accumulation of glycogen in the heart, skeletal muscles, liver, and nervous system.

results.name: Schwannomatosis
results.definition: A rare genetic disorder characterized by the presence of multiple schwannomas.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Breast Adenocarcinoma
results.definition: The most common histologic type of breast carcinoma. Representative examples include invasive ductal carcinoma not otherwise specified, ductal carcinoma in situ, inflammatory carcinoma, secretory carcinoma, signet ring cell carcinoma, tubular carcinoma, invasive lobular carcinoma, and lobular carcinoma in situ.
children: Mixed Lobular and Ductal Breast Carcinoma
Breast Adenocarcinoma with Spindle Cell Metaplasia

results.name: Thymic Mucoepidermoid Carcinoma
results.definition: A rare primary thymic carcinoma, characterized by the presence of squamous cells, intermediate type cells, and mucus-producing cells. Published information on clinical course is limited to single-case reports.

results.name: Central Nervous System Hematopoietic Neoplasm
match: Hematopoietic Neoplasm of Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Neoplasm of the Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Tumor of Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Tumor of the Central Nervous System
Lymphomas and Hemopoietic Neoplasms of CNS
Lymphomas and Hemopoietic Neoplasms of the CNS
search: Hematopoietic Neoplasm of Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Neoplasm of the Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Tumor of Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Tumor of the Central Nervous System
Lymphomas and Hemopoietic Neoplasms of CNS
Lymphomas and Hemopoietic Neoplasms of the CNS
results.definition: A primary or metastatic neoplasm of hematopoietic origin that affects the brain, meninges, or spinal cord. Representative examples include Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphomas, histiocytic tumors, and leukemias.
synonyms: Hematopoietic Neoplasm of Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Neoplasm of the Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Tumor of Central Nervous System
Hematopoietic Tumor of the Central Nervous System
Lymphomas and Hemopoietic Neoplasms of CNS
Lymphomas and Hemopoietic Neoplasms of the CNS

results.name: Intraductal Breast Myoepitheliosis
results.definition: A neoplastic process characterized by the proliferation of spindle to cuboidal myoepithelial cells within small breast ducts.

results.name: Vaginal Glandular Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of neoplastic glandular epithelial cells. Representative examples include adenoma, endometrioid adenocarcinoma, and clear cell adenocarcinoma.

results.name: Trochlear Nerve Neoplasm
match: Neoplasm of the Fourth Cranial Nerve
Tumor of the Fourth Cranial Nerve
search: Neoplasm of the Fourth Cranial Nerve
Tumor of the Fourth Cranial Nerve
synonyms: Neoplasm of the Fourth Cranial Nerve
Tumor of the Fourth Cranial Nerve

results.name: Acute Cervicitis
results.definition: Acute inflammation of the cervix. Clinical manifestations include mucopurulent vaginal discharge and burning sensation.

results.name: Telangiectatic Osteosarcoma
results.definition: An osteosarcoma usually arising from the metaphysis of long bones. It is characterized by the presence of a cystic architecture with blood-filled spaces. The prognosis is similar to that of conventional osteosarcoma.
ancestors: Malignant Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Nipple Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises in the area of the nipple.

results.name: HIV Infection
results.definition: An infection caused by the human immunodeficiency virus.
results.glossary_definition: any state accompanied by evidence of HIV in the body (positive test for HIV genome, cDNA, proteins, antigens, or antibodies); may be medically asymptomatic or symptomatic; prefer AIDS when appropriate.

results.name: Pseudomyxoma Peritonei
results.definition: A usually well differentiated mucinous adenocarcinoma of the peritoneum. The majority of cases represent tumor spread from a primary low grade mucinous neoplasm of the appendix. Cases of pseudomyxoma peritonei associated with mucinous adenocarcinomas of the gallbladder, stomach, colon, rectum, pancreas, lung, breast, and fallopian tubes have also been reported. In the past, the ovary has been considered as a common primary site associated with pseudomyxoma peritonei. However, there is recent evidence based on immunohistochemistry and molecular genetic analysis suggesting that most cases of pseudomyxoma peritonei probably represent metastasis from an appendiceal and not ovarian primary.
results.glossary_definition: A build-up of mucus in the peritoneal cavity. The mucus may come from ruptured ovarian cysts, from the appendix, or from other abdominal tissues. Mucus-secreting cells may attach to the peritoneal lining and continue to secrete mucus.

results.name: Adenoid Cystic Skin Carcinoma
match: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Skin
search: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Skin
synonyms: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Skin

results.name: Hereditary Corneal Dystrophy
results.definition: A family of inherited disorders characterized by the gradual, progressive accumulation of extraneous material on one or both corneas, which, without proper treatment, can impair vision.
results.glossary_definition: Bilateral hereditary disorders of the cornea, usually autosomal dominant, which may be present at birth but more frequently develop during adolescence and progress slowly throughout life. Central macular dystrophy is transmitted as an autosomal recessive defect.

results.name: Bilateral Retinoblastoma
results.definition: Retinoblastoma involving both eyes. This occurs in the majority of patients with the inherited variant. A minority of patient with bilateral retinoblastoma were found to have involvement of the pineal gland as well.

results.name: Gingival Recession
results.definition: A loss of gum tissue resulting in an exposure of the roots of the teeth.

results.name: Intellectual Disability
results.definition: A broad category of disorders characterized by an impairment to the intelligence an individual possesses. These impairments can result from trauma, birth, or disease and are not restricted to any particular age group.

results.name: Advanced Malignant Mesothelioma
results.definition: A malignant mesothelioma that has spread beyond its original site of growth.
results.glossary_definition: Malignant mesothelioma (cancer that forms in the lining of the chest or abdomen) that is stage II, stage III, or stage IV.

results.name: Fragile X Syndrome
results.definition: A genetic syndrome caused by mutations in the FMR1 gene which is responsible for the expression of the fragile X mental retardation 1 protein. This protein participates in neural development. This syndrome is manifested with mental, emotional, behavioral, physical, and learning disabilities.

results.name: Multiple Intraspinal Meningiomas
match: Multiple Meningiomas of Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord
Multiple Meningiomas of the Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord
Multiple Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord Meningiomas
search: Multiple Meningiomas of Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord
Multiple Meningiomas of the Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord
Multiple Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord Meningiomas
results.definition: Multiple meningiomas that arises from the spinal meninges.
synonyms: Multiple Meningiomas of Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord
Multiple Meningiomas of the Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord
Multiple Spinal Canal and Spinal Cord Meningiomas
parents: Spinal Canal And Spinal Cord Meningioma
ancestors: Spinal Canal And Spinal Cord Meningioma

results.name: Brain Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises from or metastasizes to the brain.
results.glossary_definition: The growth of abnormal cells in the tissues of the brain. Brain tumors can be benign (not cancer) or malignant (cancer).

results.name: Bronchiectasis
results.definition: Segmental, irreversible dilation of the bronchial tree resulting in the accumulation of secretions which leads to obstruction. The most common cause is bacterial infection.
results.glossary_definition: Segmental, irreversible dilation of the bronchial tree.

results.name: Testicular Trophoblastic Tumor
results.definition: A tumor that arises from the testis and is composed of neoplastic trophoblastic cells. The vast majority of cases are choriocarcinomas.

results.name: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma
match: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma/Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma/High-Grade Spindle Cell Sarcoma
Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of Soft Tissue and Bone
Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of the Soft Tissue and Bone
search: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma/Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma/High-Grade Spindle Cell Sarcoma
Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of Soft Tissue and Bone
Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of the Soft Tissue and Bone
results.oncotree_disease: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma/Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma/High-Grade Spindle Cell Sarcoma
results.definition: An undifferentiated soft tissue sarcoma characterized by the presence of a pleomorphic malignant cellular infiltrate. It is also known as malignant fibrous histiocytoma.
results.glossary_definition: A soft tissue sarcoma that usually occurs in the limbs, most commonly the legs, and may also occur in the abdomen.
synonyms: Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of Soft Tissue and Bone
Malignant Fibrous Histiocytoma of the Soft Tissue and Bone
children: Undifferentiated High Grade Pleomorphic Sarcoma of Bone
Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells

results.name: Biliary Atresia
results.definition: A congenital disorder characterized by blockage or absence of the intrahepatic or extrahepatic bile ducts.
results.glossary_definition: Atresia of the biliary tract, most commonly of the extrahepatic bile ducts.

results.name: Cerebellar Pilocytic Astrocytoma
results.definition: A WHO Grade 1 astrocytoma which arises in the cerebellum. The tumor is composed of spindle shaped cells with numerous collections of reddish astrocytic fibers called Rosenthal fibers. Over 80% or the cerebellar astrocytomas of childhood are pilocytic. Pilocytic astrocytomas may rarely occur in adults. They are usually treated by surgical resection and in most cases have a favorable prognosis.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Accessory Urethral Gland Carcinoma
results.definition: Malignant epithelial tumor arising in the accessory urethral glands.

results.name: Felty Syndrome
results.definition: A syndrome characterized by the presence of rheumatoid arthritis, splenomegaly, and granulocytopenia. Patients are at an increased risk of infection because of the low white cell counts.

results.name: Intravenous Leiomyomatosis
results.definition: A rare benign neoplasm characterized by the presence of smooth muscle cells growing within veins.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Inverted Follicular Keratosis
results.definition: Seborrheic keratosis that arises from follicular structures in the skin. It presents as a solitary nodule in the skin and is characterized by the presence of prominent squamous eddies.

results.name: Endometrial Endometrioid Adenocarcinoma with Spindled Epithelial Cells
results.name_text: Endometrial Endometrioid Adenocarcinoma with Spindled Epithelial Cells
match: Endometrial Endometrioid Adenocarcinoma with Spindled Epithelial Cells
Endometrial Endometrioid Adenocarcinoma with Spindled Epithelial Cells
search: Endometrial Endometrioid Adenocarcinoma with Spindled Epithelial Cells
Endometrial Endometrioid Adenocarcinoma with Spindled Epithelial Cells
results.definition: A primary endometrioid adenocarcinoma of the endometrium characterized by the presence of spindled malignant epithelial cells.
synonyms: Endometrial Endometrioid Adenocarcinoma with Spindled Epithelial Cells

results.name: Parathyroid Gland Mixed Cell Type Adenoma

results.name: Transient Global Amnesia
results.definition: A condition characterized by sudden, temporary, usually short-lived memory loss, not associated with a neurologic disorder. Affected individuals lose memory function for recent events and have a decreased ability to retain new information. It is usually a solitary event.

results.name: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma, Inflammatory Variant
results.definition: An undifferentiated pleomorphic sarcoma characterized by the presence of numerous inflammatory cells.

results.name: Vaginal Leiomyosarcoma
results.definition: An aggressive malignant smooth muscle neoplasm, arising from the vagina. It is characterized by a proliferation of neoplastic spindle cells.

results.name: Thyroid Gland Malformation
results.definition: An anatomic abnormality of the thyroid gland.

results.name: Cocaine Dependence
results.definition: A psychologically and socially impaired state, with or without physiological changes, that develops as a result of using cocaine and which leads to compulsive behaviors to acquire the substance.

results.name: Functioning Pituitary Gland Adenoma
match: Functioning Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Secretory Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
search: Functioning Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Secretory Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
results.definition: A hormone producing pituitary gland adenoma, associated with a hormonal syndrome.
synonyms: Functioning Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland
Secretory Adenoma of the Pituitary Gland

results.name: Breast Hemangioma
results.definition: A capillary or cavernous hemangioma arising from the breast.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Salivary Gland Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma
match: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of Salivary Gland
Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Salivary Gland
search: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of Salivary Gland
Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Salivary Gland
results.definition: An adenoid cystic carcinoma arising from the salivary gland. It is characterized by the presence of epithelial and myoepithelial cells forming tubular, cribriform, and solid patterns. It usually presents as a slow growing mass. Patients may experience pain because of the tumor propensity for perineural invasion. The tumor may follow an aggressive clinical course with recurrences and mestastases to distant sites including lungs, bones, brain, and liver.
synonyms: Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of Salivary Gland
Adenoid Cystic Carcinoma of the Salivary Gland

results.name: Albright's Hereditary Osteodystrophy
match: Albright's Hereditary Osteodystrophy with Multiple Hormone Resistance
search: Albright's Hereditary Osteodystrophy with Multiple Hormone Resistance
results.definition: A rare, autosomal dominant syndrome caused by mutations in the GNAS gene. It is characterized by the presence of short stature, obesity, round face, brachydactyly, subcutaneous ossifications, and pseudohypoparathtyroidism.
synonyms: Albright's Hereditary Osteodystrophy with Multiple Hormone Resistance

results.name: Metachronous Wilms Tumor
match: Metachronous Wilms Tumor of the Kidney
search: Metachronous Wilms Tumor of the Kidney
results.definition: Wilms tumor arising in the remaining kidney following treatment of the original Wilms tumor.
synonyms: Metachronous Wilms Tumor of the Kidney

results.name: Paratyphoid Fever
results.definition: A condition resembling typhoid fever that is caused by infection by Salmonella enterica serovar Parathyphi.
results.glossary_definition: A prolonged febrile illness commonly caused by several Paratyphi serotypes of SALMONELLA ENTERICA. It is similar to TYPHOID FEVER but less severe.

results.name: Hyperlipidemia
results.definition: Elevated levels of lipids in the blood.
results.glossary_definition: An excess of lipids in the blood.

results.name: Tricuspid Valve Insufficiency
results.definition: Dysfunction of the pulmonary valve characterized by incomplete valve closure.
results.glossary_definition: Incomplete closure of the tricuspid valve, resulting in tricuspid regurgitation; it is usually secondary to systolic overload in the right ventricle.

results.name: Membranous Glomerulonephritis
results.definition: A slowly progressive inflammation of the glomeruli characterized by immune complex deposits at the glomerular basement membrane, resulting in a thickened membrane, and nephrotic syndrome.
results.glossary_definition: characterized histologically by proteinaceous deposits on the glomerular capillary basement membrane or by thickening of the membrane; clinically similar to chronic glomerulonephritis, occasionally with transient nephrotic syndrome.

results.name: Lacrimal Gland Mucoepidermoid Carcinoma
match: Mucoepidermoid Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland
search: Mucoepidermoid Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland
results.definition: An extremely rare carcinoma that arises from the lacrimal gland. It is characterized by the presence of infiltrating nests of epidermoid cells and mucus producing cells.
synonyms: Mucoepidermoid Carcinoma of the Lacrimal Gland

results.name: Placental Choriocarcinoma
results.definition: Choriocarcinoma that develops in the placenta. It is the rarest form of gestational choriocarcinoma. Metastases to the mother and infant may occur.

results.name: Atypical Breast Papilloma
results.definition: An intraductal papilloma of the breast characterized by the presence of focal epithelial atypia.

results.name: Notochordal Tumor
results.definition: A bone tumor arising from the remnants of the fetal notochord. This category includes the chordoma and benign notochordal cell tumor.

results.name: Petit Mal Epilepsy
results.definition: Epilepsy characterized by very brief episodes of sudden cessation of activity, usually associated with eye blinking. There is no loss of the muscle tone.
results.glossary_definition: A childhood seizure disorder characterized by rhythmic electrical brain discharges of generalized onset. Clinical features include a sudden cessation of ongoing activity usually without loss of postural tone. Rhythmic blinking of the eyelids or lip smacking frequently accompanies the seizure. The usual duration is 5-10 seconds, and multiple episodes may occur daily. Juvenile absence epilepsy is characterized by the juvenile onset of absence seizures and an increased incidence of myoclonus and tonic-clonic seizures. (Menkes, Textbook of Child Neurology, 5th ed., p736)

results.name: Demyelinating Polyneuropathy
results.definition: Polyneuropathy that is characterized by demyelination of axons.

results.name: Persistent Mullerian Duct Syndrome
results.definition: The presence of Mullerian duct-derived structures in a phenotypically male individual.

results.name: Adult Brain Stem Glioma
match: Glioma of the Adult Brain Stem
search: Glioma of the Adult Brain Stem
synonyms: Glioma of the Adult Brain Stem
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Colon Lymphoma
results.definition: An extranodal lymphoma that arises from the colon. The majority are B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphomas.

results.name: Generalized Epilepsy with Febrile Seizures Plus
results.name_text: Generalized Epilepsy with Febrile Seizures Plus
match: Generalized Epilepsy with Febrile Seizures Plus
Generalized Epilepsy with Febrile Seizures Plus
search: Generalized Epilepsy with Febrile Seizures Plus
Generalized Epilepsy with Febrile Seizures Plus
results.definition: A rare, genetically heterogeneous disorder caused by mutations in the SCN1A, GABRG2, GABRD, SCN9A, or STX1B genes. It is characterized by early childhood onset febrile seizures, generalized tonic-clonic seizures, absence seizures, myoclonic seizures, and atonic seizures
synonyms: Generalized Epilepsy with Febrile Seizures Plus

results.name: Loiasis
results.definition: Infection by the African eye worm, Loa loa.
results.glossary_definition: A parasitic infection caused by the nematode Loa loa. The vector in the transmission of this infection is the horsefly (Tabanus) or the deerfly or mango fly (Chrysops). The larvae may be seen just beneath the skin or passing through the conjunctiva. Eye lesions are not uncommon. The disease is generally mild and painless.

results.name: Salivary Cyst
results.definition: A benign cyst located in the salivary gland that is lined by epithelium and filled with mucoid fluid, tissue, or other material; it is usually caused by duct obstruction.

results.name: Dravet Syndrome
results.definition: A severe form of epilepsy that presents in early childhood and is characterized by frequent, prolonged febrile or myoclonic seizures that may progress to status epilepticus and poor development of language, motor, and socialization skills.
results.glossary_definition: A severe form of epilepsy that presents in early childhood and is characterized by frequent, prolonged febrile or myoclonic seizures that may progress to status epilepticus and poor development of language, motor, and socialization skills.

results.name: Refractory Hematologic Malignancy
results.definition: A hematologic malignancy that is resistant to treatment.

results.name: Malignant Maxillary Sinus Neoplasm
match: Malignant Neoplasm of the Maxillary Sinus
Malignant Tumor of the Maxillary Sinus
search: Malignant Neoplasm of the Maxillary Sinus
Malignant Tumor of the Maxillary Sinus
results.definition: A primary or metastatic malignant neoplasm involving the maxillary sinus.
synonyms: Malignant Neoplasm of the Maxillary Sinus
Malignant Tumor of the Maxillary Sinus
ancestors: Paranasal Sinus and Nasal Cavity Cancer

results.name: Vaginal Adenosarcoma
results.definition: A malignant mixed epithelial and mesenchymal neoplasm that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of a malignant mesenchymal component and a benign or atypical mullerian-type epithelial component.
ancestors: Malignant Vaginal Mixed Epithelial and Mesenchymal Neoplasm

results.name: Eyelid Melanoma
results.definition: A melanoma that arises from the upper or lower eyelid.

results.name: Sea-Blue Histiocyte Syndrome
results.definition: A rare, inherited or acquired syndrome characterized by the presence of histiocytes in the bone marrow which contain granules stained blue with hematoxylin-eosin stain, mild thrombocytopenia and purpura, and splenomegaly.

results.name: Suprasellar Meningioma
results.definition: A meningioma that affects the suprasellar region.

results.name: Chorioamnionitis
results.definition: A morphologic finding indicating inflammation of the fetal sac membranes. It is characterized by neutrophilic infiltration of the amnion and chorion.
results.glossary_definition: Inflammation of the fetal sac membranes.

results.name: Ovarian Mucinous Cystadenofibroma
results.definition: A benign neoplasm of the ovary characterized by the presence of cystic structures lined by mucinous columnar epithelial cells in a fibrotic stroma.

results.name: Campomelic Dysplasia
results.definition: A genetic congenital disorder characterized by bowing and angulation of the long bones. It may be associated with other skeletal and extraskeletal defects.

results.name: Selective Immunoglobulin Isotype Deficiency
results.definition: A broad classification of dysgammaglobulinemias characterized by low or undetectable serum levels of one of the five immunoglobulin classes. Deficiencies of immunoglobulins present variably according to isotype. Selective deficiencies may be caused by decreased or inefficient production from progenitor B cells without any corresponding decreases in the other isotypes. The clinical course and prognosis is dependent upon the severity of the selective deficiency and associated morbidity.

match: Medullary Carcinoma of the Thyroid Gland
search: Medullary Carcinoma of the Thyroid Gland
synonyms: Medullary Carcinoma of the Thyroid Gland
results.definition: A neuroendocrine carcinoma arising from the C-cells of the thyroid gland. It is closely associated with multiple endocrine neoplasia syndromes. Approximately 10% to 20% of medullary thyroid carcinomas are familial. Patients usually present with a thyroid nodule that is painless and firm. In the majority of cases nodal involvement is present at diagnosis. Surgery is the preferred treatment for both primary lesions and recurrences. This carcinoma is generally not very sensitive to radiation and almost unresponsive to chemotherapy.
results.glossary_definition: Cancer that develops in C cells of the thyroid. The C cells make a hormone (calcitonin) that helps maintain a healthy level of calcium in the blood.
results.name: Thyroid Gland Medullary Carcinoma
Bartholin Gland Adenosquamous Carcinoma
results.definition: A carcinoma that arises from the Bartholin gland and is characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelial cells and malignant squamous epithelial cells.

results.name: Supraglottic Verrucous Carcinoma
results.reporting_disease: Head and Neck Squamous Cell Carcinoma
results.definition: An exophytic, slow growing, well differentiated and non-metastasizing squamous cell carcinoma with pushing margins that arises from the supraglottic area of the larynx.
ancestors: Head and Neck Squamous Cell Carcinoma

results.name: Favus
results.definition: A severe, chronic fungal skin infection, usually of the scalp, characterized by the development of thick, yellow cup-shaped crusts and scarring over hair follicles.

results.name: Small Intestinal Neuroendocrine Neoplasm
results.definition: A neoplasm with neuroendocrine differentiation that arises from the small intestine. It includes well differentiated neuroendocrine tumors (low and intermediate grade) and poorly differentiated neuroendocrine carcinomas (high grade).

results.name: Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever
results.definition: A viral hemorrhagic fever that is caused by the Ebola virus, which is transmitted by contact with infected animals or humans; it is characterized by high fever, unexplained bleeding, and a high mortality rate.

results.name: Cervical Adenomyoma
results.definition: A rare, benign, usually polypoid neoplasm that arises from the cervix. It is characterized by the presence of a glandular component and a smooth muscle cell component. Variants include the endocervical type, endometrial type, and atypical polypoid adenomyoma.

results.name: Ampulla of Vater Adenosquamous Carcinoma
results.definition: A carcinoma with glandular and squamous differentiation arising from the ampulla of Vater. Signs and symptoms include jaundice, abdominal pain, anorexia, nausea, vomiting, and weight loss.

results.name: Celiac Disease
results.definition: An autoimmune genetic disorder with an unknown pattern of inheritance that primarily affects the digestive tract. It is caused by intolerance to dietary gluten. Consumption of gluten protein triggers an immune response which damages small intestinal villi and prevents adequate absorption of nutrients. Clinical signs include abdominal cramping, diarrhea or constipation and weight loss. If untreated, the clinical course may progress to malnutrition, anemia, osteoporosis and an increased risk of intestinal malignancies. However, the prognosis is favorable with successful avoidance of gluten in the diet.
results.glossary_definition: A digestive disease that is caused by an immune response to a protein called gluten, which is found in wheat, rye, barley, and oats. Celiac disease damages the lining of the small intestine and interferes with the absorption of nutrients from food. A person with celiac disease may become malnourished no matter how much food is consumed.

results.name: Apocrine Adenoma
results.definition: A benign epithelial neoplasm arising from the apocrine sweat glands. Representative examples include tubular apocrine adenoma and external auditory canal ceruminous adenoma.

results.name: Stage 0 Colon Cancer
match: Carcinoma in situ of the Colon
search: Carcinoma in situ of the Colon
results.definition: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ: intraepithelial or invasion of lamina propria. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th and 7th eds.)
synonyms: Carcinoma in situ of the Colon

results.name: Mediastinal Sarcoma
results.definition: A rare sarcoma that arises from the mediastinum. Examples include liposarcoma, leiomyosarcoma, and angiosarcoma.

results.name: Perineurioma
results.definition: A rare, almost always benign tumor composed entirely of neoplastic perineurial cells. It may occur in the soft tissues, intraneurally or in mucosal sites.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Camurati-Engelmann Syndrome
results.definition: An autosomal dominant skeletal disorder caused by mutations in the TGFB1 gene. It is characterized by thickening of the bones, particularly the long bones of the extremities. It is associated with muscle weakness and tiredness.

results.name: Eosinophilic Endomyocardial Disease
results.definition: A disorder characterised by persistent eosinophilia and acute endocardial lesions, which may progress to endomyocardial fibrosis; most cases are idopathic, but there is some association with malignant tumors.

results.name: Crescentic Glomerulonephritis
results.definition: A histopathologic term for a pattern of diseases characterized by extensive crescent formation in the glomeruli; patients present clinically with rapid deterioration of renal function, and possible progression to end-stage renal failure within weeks or months.

results.name: Acute Cystitis
results.definition: An acute infection of the bladder. It is usually caused by bacteria. Signs and symptoms include increased frequency of urination, pain or burning during urination, fever, cloudy or bloody urine, and suprapubic pain.

results.name: Bartholin Gland Adenomyoma
results.definition: A rare, benign neoplasm that arises from the Bartholin gland and is characterized by the presence of a fibromuscular stroma and glands lined by mucin-secreting epithelial cells, arranged in a lobular architecture.

results.name: Cerebellar Neoplasm
results.definition: A benign or malignant (primary or metastatic) tumor involving the cerebellum. -- 2003
results.glossary_definition: Primary or metastatic neoplasms of the CEREBELLUM. Tumors in this location frequently present with ATAXIA or signs of INTRACRANIAL HYPERTENSION due to obstruction of the fourth ventricle. Common primary cerebellar tumors include fibrillary ASTROCYTOMA and cerebellar HEMANGIOBLASTOMA. The cerebellum is a relatively common site for tumor metastases from the lung, breast, and other distant organs. (From Okazaki & Scheithauer, Atlas of Neuropathology, 1988, p86 and p141)

results.name: Skin Epithelioid Hemangioma
results.definition: A hemangioma arising from the skin. It is characterized by the presence of epithelioid endothelial cells.

results.name: Ascending Cholangitis
results.definition: Acute infection of the bile ducts caused by bacteria ascending from the small intestine.

results.name: Vulvar Trichoepithelioma
results.definition: A benign neoplasm that arises from the vulva and is characterized by the presence of nests of monomorphic basaloid cells forming small cysts that contain keratin.

results.name: Columnar Cell Variant Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma
results.name_text: Columnar Cell Variant Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma
match: Columnar Cell Variant Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma
Columnar Cell Variant Papillary Thyroid Gland Carcinoma
Columnar Cell Variant Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma
search: Columnar Cell Variant Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma
Columnar Cell Variant Papillary Thyroid Gland Carcinoma
Columnar Cell Variant Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma
results.definition: A morphologic variant of papillary carcinoma of the thyroid gland characterized by the presence of pseudostratified malignant follicular cells.
synonyms: Columnar Cell Variant Papillary Thyroid Gland Carcinoma
Columnar Cell Variant Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma

results.name: Propionic Acidemia
results.definition: A rare autosomal inherited organic acid disorder caused by mutations in the PCCA and PCCB genes. It results in the accumulation of harmful organic acids in the blood and urine. Signs and symptoms appear in infancy and include vomiting, poor feeding, loss of appetite, hypotonia, and lethargy.

results.name: Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
results.name_text: Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
match: Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
Epidermoid Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
search: Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
Epidermoid Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
results.definition: A squamous cell carcinoma arising from the penis. It occurs chiefly in the squamous epithelium of the glans, coronal sulcus, and foreskin. Etiologic factors include phimosis, lichen sclerosus, smoking, ultraviolet irradiation, history of warts or condylomas, and lack of circumcision. Human papilloma virus is present in a subset of penile squamous cell carcinomas. Patients may present with an exophytic or flat ulcerative mass in the glans or a large primary tumor with inguinal nodal and skin metastases. Morphologic variants include the basaloid carcinoma, warty (condylomatous) carcinoma, verrucous carcinoma, and sarcomatoid (spindle cell) carcinoma. (WHO, 2004)
synonyms: Epidermoid Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis
children: Mixed Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Penis

results.name: Diencephalic Astrocytoma
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Hair Disorder
results.definition: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder involving the hair. Representative examples include folliculitis, alopecia, tricholemmoma, and pilomatrical carcinoma.
results.glossary_definition: Diseases affecting the orderly growth and persistence of hair.

results.definition: An aggressive, usually diffuse non-Hodgkin lymphoma composed of small to medium sized B-lymphocytes (centrocytes). Most patients present with advanced stage disease with lymphadenopathy, hepatosplenomegaly, and bone marrow involvement. The gastrointestinal tract is the most commonly affected extranodal site by this type of non-Hodgkin lymphoma. The vast majority of cases express the t(11;14)(q13;q32) resulting in the rearrangement of the BCL-1 gene and the overexpression of cyclin D1 mRNA.
results.glossary_definition: An aggressive (fast-growing) type of B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma that usually occurs in middle-aged or older adults. It is marked by small- to medium-size cancer cells that may be in the lymph nodes, spleen, bone marrow, blood, and gastrointestinal system.
results.name: Mantle Cell Lymphoma
Cannabis Dependence
results.definition: Physical and psychological dependence on the drug cannabis.

results.name: Inflammatory Liposarcoma
results.definition: A rare morphologic variant of well differentiated liposarcoma occurring most often in the retroperitoneum. It is characterized by the presence of a predominant inflammatory infiltrate composed of lymphoplasmacytic aggregates.

results.name: Juvenile Rheumatoid Arthritis
results.definition: An older, deprecated term that encompassed three major types of autoimmune or autoinflammatory arthritis in children: systemic-onset, pauciarticular, or polyarticular arthritis. The juvenile rheumatoid arthritis classification system has been replaced by the International League of Associations for Rheumatology (ILAR) juvenile idiopathic arthritis classification system.
results.glossary_definition: Rheumatoid arthritis of children occurring in three major subtypes defined by the symptoms present during the first six months following onset: systemic-onset (Still's Disease, Juvenile-Onset) polyarticular-onset, and pauciarticular-onset. Adult-onset cases of Still's disease (STILL'S DISEASE, ADULT-ONSET) are also known. Only one subtype of juvenile rheumatoid arthritis (polyarticular-onset, rheumatoid factor-positive) clinically resembles adult rheumatoid arthritis and is considered its childhood equivalent.

results.name: Ischemic Neuropathy
results.definition: Neuropathy that is caused by inadequate blood supply.

results.name: Melanotic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
results.name_text: Melanotic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
match: Melanotic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
Melanocytic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
Melanotic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
search: Melanotic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
Melanocytic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
Melanotic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
results.definition: A malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumor characterized by the presence of malignant cells that contain melanin and formation of psammoma bodies.
synonyms: Melanocytic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
Melanotic Psammomatous Malignant Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor

ancestors: Malignant Melanotic Peripheral Nerve Sheath Tumor
Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Ovarian Gonadoblastoma
results.definition: A neoplasm that arises from the ovary and is composed of tissues that resemble dysgerminoma or seminoma and are admixed with sex cord tissues. It is found in children or young adults and usually is associated with secondary sex organs abnormalities. The majority of patients present as phenotypic females with virilization. The minority of patients present as phenotypic males with feminization. It typically affects both gonads. If a malignant germ cell component is present, it may metastasize to other anatomic sites.

results.name: Steroid Lipomatosis
results.definition: A neoplastic process characterized by a diffuse poorly circumscribed overgrowth of adipose tissue in the face, upper middle back, and sternal region. It is associated with adrenocortical steroid therapy or an increase in endogenous adrenocortical hormone.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Lafora Disease
results.definition: A rare, fatal autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the genes EPM2A and EPM2b. It is characterized by the presence of cytoplasmic inclusion bodies called Lafora bodies in many cells of the body including neurons, muscle cells, and liver cells. The Lafora bodies contain mucopolysaccharides. Signs and symptoms include seizures, myoclonus, ataxia, and dementia.
ancestors: Variable Age At Onset Electroclinical Syndrome

results.name: Intracerebral Cystic Meningioma
results.definition: A cystic meningioma that grows within the cerebral hemispheres.

results.name: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells
results.name_text: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells
match: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells
Malignant Giant Cell Neoplasm of Soft Parts
Malignant Giant Cell Tumor of Soft Parts
Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells
search: Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells
Malignant Giant Cell Neoplasm of Soft Parts
Malignant Giant Cell Tumor of Soft Parts
Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells
results.definition: An undifferentiated pleomorphic sarcoma characterized by the presence of osteoclast-like giant cells and cellular pleomorphism.
synonyms: Malignant Giant Cell Neoplasm of Soft Parts
Malignant Giant Cell Tumor of Soft Parts
Undifferentiated Pleomorphic Sarcoma with Osteoclast-Like Giant Cells

results.name: Paraphimosis
results.definition: A condition in which the foreskin of an uncircumcised male is retracted and cannot be pulled back over the glans penis. It results in painful swelling of the glans penis and, if is not corrected, may lead to gangrene.
results.glossary_definition: Retraction of phimotic foreskin, causing a painful swelling of the glans that, if severe, may cause dry gangrene unless corrected. (Dorland, 27th ed)

results.name: Childhood Leptomeningeal Melanoma
results.definition: A melanoma that arises from leptomeningeal melanocytes and occurs in childhood.

results.name: Childhood Pilocytic Astrocytoma
results.definition: A pilocytic astrocytoma that occurs during childhood.
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Toxocariasis
results.definition: A parasitic infection caused by Toxocara. Humans are infected by the larvae of Toxocara canis and Toxocara cati from dogs and cats respectively. Most cases remain asymptomatic. The parasites may affect the eye, causing diminished vision, or other major organs, causing hepatomegaly, eosinophilia, wheezing, and coughing.

results.name_text: Central Nervous System Germ Cell Tumor

Central Nervous System Germ Cell Neoplasm

Germ Cell Tumor of the Central Nervous System
results.definition: A unique group of rare tumors of the central nervous system that affect mainly children and adolescents. Their morphologic and biologic profile corresponds to that of homologous germ cell tumors that arise in the gonads and in other extragonadal sites. Representative examples include: germinoma, embryonal carcinoma, yolk sac tumor, choriocarcinoma, and teratoma.

results.name: Fibrodysplasia Ossificans Progressiva
results.definition: A condition in which there is progressive heterotopic bone formation of the tendons and muscles.

results.name: Cerebellar Liponeurocytoma
results.definition: A rare, WHO grade II cerebellar neoplasm which shows consistent neuronal, variable astrocytic and focal lipomatous differentiation. It occurs in adults, has a low proliferative potential and usually has a favorable prognosis. (Adapted from WHO)
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Pancreatic Cystadenocarcinoma
results.definition: A cystic adenocarcinoma that arises from the pancreas. It includes the acinar cell and serous cystadenocarcinoma subtypes.

results.name: Central Nervous System Extraskeletal Osteosarcoma
match: Osteosarcoma of the Central Nervous System
search: Osteosarcoma of the Central Nervous System
results.definition: An osteosarcoma arising from the brain or spinal cord.
synonyms: Osteosarcoma of the Central Nervous System
parents: Central Nervous System Mesenchymal Non-meningothelial Tumor
ancestors: Central Nervous System Mesenchymal Non-meningothelial Tumor

results.name: Cutaneous Mastocytosis
results.definition: A form of mastocytosis characterized by mast cell infiltration of the skin. (WHO, 2001)

results.name: Pelvic Inflammatory Disease
results.definition: Pelvic inflammatory disease (PID) is an acute or chronic inflammation in the pelvic cavity. It is most commonly caused by sexually transmitted diseases, including chlamydia and gonorrhea that have ascended into the uterus, fallopian tubes, or ovaries as a result of intercourse or childbirth, or of surgical procedures, including insertion of IUDs or abortion. PID may be either symptomatic or asymptomatic. It may cause infertility and it may raise the risk of ectopic pregnancy. PID is a disease associated with HIV infection.
results.glossary_definition: A condition in which the female reproductive organs are inflamed. It may affect the uterus, fallopian tubes, ovaries, and certain ligaments. Pelvic inflammatory disease is usually caused by a bacterial infection. It may cause infertility and an increased risk of an ectopic pregnancy (pregnancy in the fallopian tubes).

results.name: Reactive Cutaneous Fibrous Lesion
results.definition: A benign, epidermal skin lesion characterized by overexpression of collagen during wound healing.

results.name: Pulmonary Artery Leiomyosarcoma
results.definition: An aggressive malignant smooth muscle neoplasm, arising from the pulmonary artery It is characterized by a proliferation of neoplastic spindle cells.

results.name: Asthma
results.definition: A chronic respiratory disease manifested as difficulty breathing due to the narrowing of bronchial passageways.
results.glossary_definition: A chronic disease in which the bronchial airways in the lungs become narrowed and swollen, making it difficult to breathe. Symptoms include wheezing, coughing, tightness in the chest, shortness of breath, and rapid breathing. An attack may be brought on by pet hair, dust, smoke, pollen, mold, exercise, cold air, or stress.

results.name: Oligospermia
results.definition: Decreased number of spermatozoa in the semen.
results.glossary_definition: Deficiency in the number of spermatozoa in semen. (Dorland, 27th ed)

results.name: Appendix Leiomyoma
results.definition: A well-circumscribed benign smooth muscle neoplasm arising from the appendix. It is characterized by the presence of spindle cells with cigar-shaped nuclei, interlacing fascicles, and a whorled pattern.
ancestors: Benign Connective and Soft Tissue Neoplasm

results.name: Childhood Brain Stem Glioma
match: Childhood Glioma of the Brain Stem
Pediatric Glioma of the Brain Stem
search: Childhood Glioma of the Brain Stem
Pediatric Glioma of the Brain Stem
results.definition: An abnormal growth of the cells that comprise the tissues of the brainstem. While the tumor may be histologically benign, it can produce great morbidity due to its location. It presents most commonly in the first two decades of life.
synonyms: Childhood Glioma of the Brain Stem
Pediatric Glioma of the Brain Stem
ancestors: Neuroepithelial, Perineurial, and Schwann Cell Neoplasm

results.name: Dracunculiasis
results.definition: A parasitic infection caused by Dracunculus medinensis. It is caused by drinking water contaminated with water fleas. The larvae enter the body through the intestine. Signs and symptoms include pain, edema, blisters, and ulcers.

results.name: Stress Polycythemia
results.definition: Polycythemia that is caused by stress.

results.name: Staphylococcal Food Poisoning
results.definition: Food poisoning that is caused by Staphylococcal infection.
results.glossary_definition: Poisoning by staphylococcal toxins present in contaminated food.

results.name: Central Nervous System Neoplasm
match: Neoplasm of the Central Nervous System
Tumor of the Central Nervous System
search: Neoplasm of the Central Nervous System
Tumor of the Central Nervous System
results.definition: A benign or malignant, primary or metastatic neoplasm that affects the brain, meninges, or spinal cord. Representative examples of primary neoplasms include astrocytoma, oligodendroglioma, ependymoma, and meningioma. Representative examples of metastatic neoplasms include carcinoma and leukemia.
results.glossary_definition: A tumor of the central nervous system, including brain stem glioma, craniopharyngioma, medulloblastoma, and meningioma.
synonyms: Neoplasm of the Central Nervous System
Tumor of the Central Nervous System
children: Central Nervous System Germ Cell Tumor
Central Nervous System Mesenchymal Non-meningothelial Tumor

results.name: Papillon-Lefevre Syndrome
results.definition: A rare autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the cathepsin C gene. It is manifested with periodontitis resulting in the premature loss of teeth and palmoplantar keratoderma.

results.name: Mastocytosis
results.definition: A clonal myeloproliferative neoplasm characterized by the proliferation and accumulation of neoplastic mast cells in one or multiple organs or organ systems. It is a heterogeneous group of neoplasms, ranging from cutaneous proliferations which may regress spontaneously, to aggressive neoplasms associated with organ failure and short survival.

results.name: Cherubism
match: Familial Fibrous Dysplasia of the Jaws
Familial Multilocular Cystic Disease of the Jaws
search: Familial Fibrous Dysplasia of the Jaws
Familial Multilocular Cystic Disease of the Jaws
results.definition: A rare autosomal dominant inherited disorder usually caused by mutations in the SH3BP2 gene. It is characterized by a prominent lower part of the face due to bilateral replacement of the mandibular or maxillary bones by lesions. The lesions contain osteoclast-like cells admixed with spindle-shaped mononuclear stromal cells. With time, the lesions become more fibrotic and less osteoclast-rich.
synonyms: Familial Fibrous Dysplasia of the Jaws
Familial Multilocular Cystic Disease of the Jaws

results.name: Thymic Lymphoepithelioma-Like Carcinoma
results.definition: A rare, usually aggressive primary thymic carcinoma, characterized by a syncytial growth of undifferentiated carcinoma cells and the presence of a lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate. More than 40% of cases are associated with Epstein-Barr virus infection.

results.name: Personality Disorder
results.definition: A diverse category of psychiatric disorders characterized by behavior that deviates markedly from the expectations of the individual's culture; this pattern of deviation is pervasive and inflexible and is stable over time. The behavioral pattern negatively interferes with relationships and work.
results.glossary_definition: when normal personality traits become inflexible and maladaptive, causing subjective distress or impaired social functioning, they can be considered disorders.

results.name: Pancreatic Intraductal Papillary-Mucinous Neoplasm with High Grade Dysplasia
results.name_text: Pancreatic Intraductal Papillary-Mucinous Neoplasm with High Grade Dysplasia
